Paper Code: ETCS-203
Paper: Foundation of Computer Science


UNIT- I
Formal Logic: Preposition, Symbolic Representation & logical entailment theory of inferences & tautologies, Predicates, Quantifiers, Theory of inferences for predicate calculus, resolution.
Techniques for theorem proving: Direct Proof, Proof by Contraposition, Proof by contradiction.
[T1,T2]

UNIT- II
Sets: Overview, set operations, permutation and combination, principle of inclusion, exclusion(with proof) and pigeonhole principle(with proof), Relation, operation & representation of a relation, equivalence relation, POSET, Hasse Diagrams, extremal elements, Lattices, composition of function, inverse, binary & n-ary operations.
[T1,T2]

UNIT- III
Principle of mathematical induction, principle of complete induction, solution methods for linear & non-linear 1st-order recurrence relations with constant coefficients.
Graph Theory: Terminology, isomorphic graphs, Euler’s formula(proof), chromatic number of a graph, 5-color theorem(with proof), Euler & Hamiltonian paths.
[T1,T2]

UNIT-IV
Groups, Symmetry, subgroups, normal subgroups, cyclic group, permutation group and Cayley's theorem(without proof), Cosets-Lagrange’s theorem(with proof), homomorphism, isomorphism, automorphism, rings.
Boolean function, Boolean expression, representation & minimization of Boolean function.
[T1,T2]


Text Books:
[T1] Norman L. Biggs
     “Discrete Mathematics”
      Oxford, 2d edition
[T2] Keneth H. Rosen
     “Discrete Mathematics and Its Applications”
      TMH, 7th edition

Reference Books:
[R1] Kolman, Busby & Ross
     “Discrete Mathematical Structures”
      PHI, 1996
[R2] C.L. Liu
     “Elements of Discrete Mathematics”
      TMH, 2000
[R3] J.P. Trembly & P. Manohar
     “Discrete Mathematical Structures with Applications to Computer Science”
      McGraw Hill, 1997